records.addlTxt:
Defendant Courtney Rae Nissenbaum in court with Attorney Christopher Scott Carson.  
Patricia Irene Daugherty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a serve 12 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 20 days time served.  Huber Release to the day reporting center and for inmate work assignments ONLY.  The Court notes a STRONG OBJECTION to Electronic Monitoring.

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS OF PROBATION with referral to Mental Health Unit.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and cooperate with recommended follow-up care/treatment;
*Maintain Absolute Sobriety- no possession/use of alcohol or any controlled substances, unless valid prescription and follow prescription instructions;
*DOC must conduct random urine screens/alcohol testing at least 1x per month during the entire 2 years of probation;
*Notify DOC agent of all prescriptions within 72 hours of receiving prescription from medical professional;
*Fill prescriptions at one pharmacy, unless otherwise approved by DOC agent, and notify DOC agent of the pharmacy;
*No possession of firearms, ammunition, magazine, or holster;
*Seek/maintain full time work or full time school, or full time aoda treatment or any combination equal to 40 hours;
*Obtain Mental health evaluation and cooperate with recommended follow-up care/treatment;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period-any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment- bail to apply- balance (if any) returned to remitter;
*Condition Time IMPOSED AND STAYED as follows- Serve 4 months in the House of Corrections with release to the day reporting center and for inmate work assignments ONLY.  The Court notes a STRONG OBJECTION to Electronic Monitoring- Condition time to be IMPOSED IF the defendant violates any of the following conditions: 1) missed drug test 2) failure to provide usable sample 3) positive drug test 4) possess controlled substance without valid prescription 5) possess drug paraphernalia 6) failure to comply with aoda treatment plan;

The Court instructs the Department of Corrections to develop a trauma informed care plan for the defendant.

Defendant is informed she may not possess and/or own any firearms.
Defendant is informed she may not vote in any election until her civil rights have been reinstated.  

Appeal rights given. Filed, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement, and Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
